AssociateTargetGroups.document: This API is used to bind target groups to a CLB.This is an async API. After the API return succeeds, you can call the DescribeTaskStatus API with the returned RequestID as an input parameter to check whether this task is successful.
AssociateTargetGroups.name: Associates a CLB with a target group

CreateGatewayLoadBalancer.document: This API is used to create a GWLB instance. To use the GWLB service, you must purchase one or more GWLB instances. After this API is called successfully, a unique ID for the GWLB instance will be returned.Note: The default purchase quota for each account in each region is 10.This is an async API. After the API is called successfully, you can use the DescribeGatewayLoadBalancers API to query the status of the GWLB instance (such as creating and normal) to determine whether the creation is successful.
CreateGatewayLoadBalancer.name: Purchases a GWLB Instance

CreateTargetGroup.document: This API is used to create a target group. This feature is in beta testing. If you need to use it, please [submit a ticket](https://console.cloud.tencent.com/workorder/category?level1_id=6&level2_id=163&source=0&data_title=%E8%B4%9F%E8%BD%BD%E5%9D%87%E8%A1%A1%20LB&step=1).
CreateTargetGroup.name: Creates a target group

DeleteGatewayLoadBalancer.document: This API is used to delete one or more specified GWLB instances. After successful deletion, the GWLB instances will be unbound from the backend service.This is an async API. After the API return succeeds, you can call the DescribeTaskStatus API with the returned RequestId as an input parameter to check whether this task is successful.
DeleteGatewayLoadBalancer.name: Deletes a GWLB instance

DeleteTargetGroups.document: This API is used to delete a target group.
DeleteTargetGroups.name: Deletes a target group

DeregisterTargetGroupInstances.document:
This API is used to unbind a server from a target group.
This is an async API. After the API return succeeds, you can call the DescribeTaskStatus API with the returned RequestID as an input parameter to check whether this task is successful.
DeregisterTargetGroupInstances.name: Unbinds instances in the target group

DescribeGatewayLoadBalancers.document: This API is used to query the list of GWLB instances in a region.
DescribeGatewayLoadBalancers.name: Queries the list of GWLB instances

DescribeTargetGroupInstanceStatus.document: This API is used to query the backend service status of a target group. Currently, only GWLB type target groups support querying backend service status.
DescribeTargetGroupInstanceStatus.name: Queries the backend service status of a target group

DescribeTargetGroupInstances.document: This API is used to obtain information on servers bound to a target group.
DescribeTargetGroupInstances.name: Obtains the list of instances bound to the target group

DescribeTargetGroupList.document: This API is used to obtain a target group list.
DescribeTargetGroupList.name: Obtains a target group list.

DescribeTargetGroups.document: This API is used to query target group information.
DescribeTargetGroups.name: Queries target group information

DescribeTaskStatus.document: This API is used to query the execution status of an async task. After non-query APIs (for example, used to create/delete CLB instances) are called successfully, this API needs to be used to query whether the task is successful.
DescribeTaskStatus.name: Queries the status of an async task

DisassociateTargetGroups.document: This API is used to disassociate a CLB from a target group.This is an async API. After the API return succeeds, you can call the DescribeTaskStatus API with the returned RequestID as an input parameter to check whether this task is successful.
DisassociateTargetGroups.name: Disassociates a CLB from a target group

InquirePriceCreateGatewayLoadBalancer.document: This API is used to query the price for creating a GWLB.
InquirePriceCreateGatewayLoadBalancer.name: Queries the price for purchasing a GWLB

ModifyGatewayLoadBalancerAttribute.document: This API is used to modify the attributes of a CLB instance. It supports modifying the name and bandwidth cap of the CLB instance.
ModifyGatewayLoadBalancerAttribute.name: Modifies the attributes of a GWLB instance

ModifyTargetGroupAttribute.document: This API is used to modify the name, health check, and other attributes of the target group.
ModifyTargetGroupAttribute.name: Modifies target group attributes

ModifyTargetGroupInstancesWeight.document: This API is used to modify the server weight of a target group.This is an async API. After the API return succeeds, you can call the DescribeTaskStatus API with the returned RequestID as an input parameter to check whether this task is successful.
ModifyTargetGroupInstancesWeight.name: Modifies the server weight of a target group

RegisterTargetGroupInstances.document: This API is used to register servers to a target group.This is an async API. After the API return succeeds, you can call the DescribeTaskStatus API with the returned RequestID as an input parameter to check whether this task is successful.
RegisterTargetGroupInstances.name: Adds instances to the target group
